 and friends  Welcome to the 3rd edition of the department s newsletter  We trust you will enjoy reading about the exciting things we are doing  Just click on the topic headings for the full story  With warm regards  Floyd H  Duncan  Col  Department Chairman   AACSB Accreditation Accreditation by AACSB International  the Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business  continues to be a major focus of the economics and business faculty  The Major Field Test in Business Though not up to our usual standards  the Class of 2009 performed well on the Educational Testing Service s Major Field Test Business  MFTB  Col  Husted Retires Col  Stewart Husted  professor of marketing retires from VMI  New Hire   Col  Scarpaci Dr  Joseph Scarpaci will be joining the faculty in the Fall  Faculty Research Our faculty have been hard at work publishing research in academic journals as well as presenting their research at various conferences around the country and the world  Speakers Over the past academic year  our cadets were fortunate enough to hear from several speakers both from academia and business  Cadet Research The VMI Undergraduate Research Initiative  URI  was established by directive of the Dean of Faculty to more fully integrate student scholarly inquiry into the VMI experience  The Cadet Investment Group The Cadet Investment Group  CIG  was founded in 1986 by the VMI Foundation  The group s mission is to learn about investing  To do this  members serve as investment analysts and portfolio managers  Cadet Internships In the summer of 2009  five cadets participated in the inaugural summer of the department s  internship for credit  program  SBD and ODE Activity The Sigma Beta Delta  the Honor Society for Business and Omicron Delta Economics Honor Society were quite active this past year thanks to the leadership provided by Cadets Thompson and Johnston  Cadet Awards The Annual ODE Banquet to honor our top cadets was held on April 8th  Alumni Survey Calling all members of the Classes of 1994 and 2004  Stay Connected to ECBU  Please let us know what you ve been up to by emailing us at ECBUnewsletter vmi edu  If you are interested in hosting a field trip  accepting an intern  speaking to our cadets or helping out in any way at all  just let us know  Even if you have nothing to report  send an email to let us know that you want to be on our email list  Spring 2009 Newsletter AACSB Accreditation  Major Field Test in Business  Colonel Husted Retires  New Hire   Colonel Scarpaci  Faculty Scholarship  Speakers  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  SBD and ODE Activity  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey  Stay Connected Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Social Science   Economics   Business   Economics Newsletter   Spring 2009 Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Social Science   Economics   Business   Economics Newsletter   Spring 2009 Home Academics Areas of Study Social Science Economics   Business      Economics Newsletter Spring 2009 Greetings alumni and friends  Welcome to the 3rd edition of the department s newsletter  We trust you will enjoy reading about the exciting things we are doing  Just click on the topic headings for the full story  With warm regards  Floyd H  Duncan  Col  Department Chairman   AACSB Accreditation Accreditation by AACSB International  the Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business  continues to be a major focus of the economics and business faculty  The Major Field Test in Business Though not up to our usual standards  the Class of 2009 performed well on the Educational Testing Service s Major Field Test Business  MFTB  Col  Husted Retires Col  Stewart Husted  professor of marketing retires from VMI  New Hire   Col  Scarpaci Dr  Joseph Scarpaci will be joining the faculty in the Fall  Faculty Research Our faculty have been hard at work publishing research in academic journals as well as presenting their research at various conferences around the country and the world  Speakers Over the past academic year  our cadets were fortunate enough to hear from several speakers both from academia and business  Cadet Research The VMI Undergraduate Research Initiative  URI  was established by directive of the Dean of Faculty to more fully integrate student scholarly inquiry into the VMI experience  The Cadet Investment Group The Cadet Investment Group  CIG  was founded in 1986 by the VMI Foundation  The group s mission is to learn about investing  To do this  members serve as investment analysts and portfolio managers  Cadet Internships In the summer of 2009  five cadets participated in the inaugural summer of the department s  internship for credit  program  SBD and ODE Activity The Sigma Beta Delta  the Honor Society for Business and Omicron Delta Economics Honor Society were quite active this past year thanks to the leadership provided by Cadets Thompson and Johnston  Cadet Awards The Annual ODE Banquet to honor our top cadets was held on April 8th  Alumni Survey Calling all members of the Classes of 1994 and 2004  Stay Connected to ECBU  Please let us know what you ve been up to by emailing us at ECBUnewsletter vmi edu  If you are interested in hosting a field trip  accepting an intern  speaking to our cadets or helping out in any way at all  just let us know  Even if you have nothing to report  send an email to let us know that you want to be on our email list Economics Newsletter Spring 2009 Greetings alumni and friends  Welcome to the 3rd edition of the department s newsletter  We trust you will enjoy reading about the exciting things we are doing  Just click on the topic headings for the full story  With warm regards  Floyd H  Duncan  Col  Department Chairman         AACSB Accreditation Accreditation by AACSB International  the Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business  continues to be a major focus of the economics and business faculty AACSB Accreditation AACSB Accreditation  AACSB International The Major Field Test in Business Tho